data.content:
Yes! MSTest v3.4+ supports **tuple-based `DynamicData`**, giving you compile-time type safety:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[DynamicData(nameof(TestData))]
public void Validate_ReturnsExpected(string input, bool expected)
{
    var result = Validator.IsValid(input);
    Assert.AreEqual(expected, result);
}

public static IEnumerable<(string Input, bool Expected)> TestData =>
[
    ("valid@email.com", true),
    ("invalid", false),
    ("", false),
];
```

**What changed:** The data source returns `IEnumerable<(string, bool)>` instead of `IEnumerable<object[]>`. The compiler now enforces that each entry matches the expected types — no more runtime casting or mismatched argument errors.

Requires `MSTest.TestFramework` ≥ 3.4 (or MSTest SDK ≥ 3.4).
